    {
      "id": "RQ-0029",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Automate reload and resume lifecycle regression coverage",
      "description": "Opportunity type: reliability. The repo's primary confidence path is a real Pi session driven in tmux, and the docs explicitly require configured-source validation for `/reload`, full restart, and `/resume`. That critical lifecycle path is still manual today. Why it matters: the extension's differentiating value is managed-session continuity, artifact persistence, and tab recovery across lifecycle events, so manual-only validation is the highest-confidence gap in the repo. Proposed approach: add an explicit opt-in tmux-driven lifecycle harness that launches configured-source Pi, sends prompts, exercises `/reload` and restart plus `/resume`, and asserts that the same managed browser state and spill-file paths survive. Risks and mitigations: keep the harness deterministic, isolate Pi settings and extension sources rather than mutating the operator's normal configuration unless explicitly requested, clean up tmux/browser/temp side effects, and capture transcripts for post-failure debugging instead of relying on fragile text scraping alone. Acceptance criteria: one documented opt-in script runs the configured-source lifecycle checks end to end, emits actionable transcript artifacts on failure, covers same-page continuity plus persisted `fullOutputPath` survival, proves updated extension-code pickup via a deterministic sentinel or equivalent mechanism, and performs best-effort cleanup.",
      "priority": "high",
      "tags": [
        "innovation",
        "reliability",
        "lifecycle",
        "automation"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "AGENTS.md",
        "docs/RELEASE.md",
        "docs/REQUIREMENTS.md",
        "package.json",
        "scripts",
        "test"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: AGENTS.md :: Preferred testing workflow :: the primary confidence path is an end-to-end Pi run inside tmux with separate isolated and configured-source lifecycle modes",
        "path: docs/RELEASE.md :: Configured-source lifecycle validation :: maintainers are told to manually exercise `/reload`, restart, and `/resume` to validate managed-session continuity and persisted spill paths",
        "path: package.json :: scripts :: there is no lifecycle or tmux automation entrypoint alongside `verify`, `verify:package:pi`, or `verify:release`"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define a deterministic opt-in lifecycle scenario that proves managed-session continuity, persisted artifact survival, and updated extension code pickup without depending on the operator's normal Pi settings.",
        "Implement a tmux-driven harness that launches configured-source Pi with an isolated source configuration, submits prompts, restarts Pi, resumes the session, and captures transcripts.",
        "Add assertions for same-page continuity, persisted spill-file reachability, updated-code sentinel visibility, and clear failure logs.",
        "Document when to use the automated lifecycle harness versus isolated quick smoke mode, including cleanup and transcript retention behavior.",
        "Verify by running the new lifecycle command and confirming it passes on a healthy setup, cleans up tmux/browser/temp artifacts, and produces usable transcript evidence on an injected failure."
      ],
      "notes": [],
