    {
      "id": "RQ-0033",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Render file artifacts beyond screenshots",
      "description": "Opportunity type: feature gap. The extension already inlines screenshots and summarizes direct download and pdf outputs, but other file-producing upstream commands such as `trace`, `profiler`, `record`, and network HAR capture remain generic pass-throughs. Why it matters: artifact-heavy debugging and QA workflows are one of the clearest advantages of a native browser tool, and generic file output makes those workflows harder to inspect, compare, and hand off. Proposed approach: after confirming real upstream output shapes, add a unified metadata-first artifact renderer that recognizes supported file-producing commands, returns saved-path plus file-type metadata, and provides lightweight previews only where safe without bloating context. Risks and mitigations: treat artifact rendering as metadata-first so large binaries stay out of model context unless there is a safe inline preview, and keep the shared artifact shape reusable by async downloads and future inventory work. Acceptance criteria: representative file-producing commands return readable artifact summaries with structured paths and types, batch flows preserve per-step artifact metadata, network HAR output is included if upstream exposes a path-bearing shape, and tests cover at least trace, profiler, record, and screenshot behavior together.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "innovation",
        "feature-gap",
        "artifacts",
        "qa"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/shared.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts",
        "docs/TOOL_CONTRACT.md",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md :: Diff, debug, and streaming :: `trace`, `profiler`, `record`, and related file-producing commands are part of the documented upstream surface",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts :: extractImagePath :: only screenshot outputs are currently trusted for inline attachment behavior",
        "path: test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts :: coverage :: artifact-focused tests cover screenshots, downloads, and pdfs but not trace, profiler, record, or HAR-style outputs"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Define a shared artifact metadata shape that works for screenshot, pdf, download, wait-based download, trace, profiler, record, network HAR, and future file-producing commands.",
        "Implement artifact-family rendering that preserves saved paths, file type hints, and safe inline previews where appropriate.",
        "Extend batch rendering so file artifacts remain inspectable per step.",
        "Add tests for representative non-screenshot artifact commands and update docs to describe the new behavior.",
        "Verify by running presentation tests and checking that representative artifact commands return concise summaries with stable structured paths."
      ],
