    {
      "id": "RQ-0034",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Surface actionable confirm and deny recovery flows",
      "description": "Opportunity type: reliability. The tracked upstream surface includes guarded-action confirmation primitives such as `confirm <id>`, `deny <id>`, and `--confirm-actions`, but the wrapper does not yet make pending confirmations feel actionable inside Pi. Right now an agent can discover the command family in docs, but not through a first-class recovery experience. Why it matters: guarded actions are a safety feature, and the native tool should help agents finish those flows correctly instead of dropping them into generic details blobs. Proposed approach: after capturing the upstream confirmation-needed result shape, detect confirmation-needed outputs, render the pending action id and next-step commands clearly, and add docs and tests for approval and denial recovery. Risks and mitigations: keep the wrapper thin by surfacing upstream ids and next calls rather than inventing a second confirmation model, and preserve redaction for sensitive action context. Acceptance criteria: pending confirmation results are rendered with the id and follow-up examples, the wrapper keeps redaction intact for sensitive confirmation contexts, and tests cover both confirm and deny paths.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "innovation",
        "reliability",
        "safety",
        "workflow"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts",
        "extensions/agent-browser/lib/results/presentation.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.presentation.test.ts",
        "test/agent-browser.extension-validation.test.ts",
        "docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: docs/COMMAND_REFERENCE.md :: Batch, auth, confirmations, sessions, chat, dashboard, and setup :: `confirm <id>`, `deny <id>`, and `--confirm-actions` are part of the supported surface",
        "path: extensions/agent-browser/lib/runtime.ts :: GLOBAL_FLAGS_WITH_VALUES :: the wrapper already accepts `--confirm-actions` as part of raw upstream argument planning",
        "path: README.md :: Agent quick start :: there is no documented recovery pattern or first-class example for pending confirmation flows"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Identify the upstream confirmation-needed result shape from real-upstream evidence and the minimum native recovery UX needed for Pi.",
        "Add rendering that prints the pending confirmation id and the exact follow-up `confirm` or `deny` tool calls without exposing redaction-sensitive context.",
        "Cover confirm-required success and failure paths in tests, including redaction-sensitive scenarios.",
        "Document the safety workflow in the command reference or tool contract without expanding into a new wrapper-specific action model.",
        "Verify by running the new confirmation tests and confirming a pending-action result now contains the id and the correct next-step calls."
      ],
